    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2cc7a324_75b2b32d",
        "filename": "infra/bots/recipe_modules/docker/api.py",
        "patchSetId": 10
      },
      "lineNbr": 83,
      "author": {
        "id": 10815
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-16T15:23:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Changed the comment and commented on the function, practically that wouldn\u0027t help, since src_dir would still has to be an ancestor of self.m.path[\u0027start_dir\u0027], or else it won\u0027t be in the container.\n\nThe relpath here is effectively removing self.m.path[\u0027start_dir\u0027] so it can be replaced with \u0027/SRC\u0027. As an example:\nself.m.path[\u0027start_dir\u0027]  \u003d\u003d  \u0027/mnt/pd0/s/w/ir\u0027\nsrc_dir \u003d\u003d \u0027/mnt/pd0/s/w/ir\u0027\nscript \u003d\u003d\u0027/mnt/pd0/s/w/ir/recipe_bundle/path/to/script.sh\u0027\n\nposixpath.relpath(str(script), str(self.m.path[\u0027start_dir\u0027])) \u003d\u003d \u0027recipe_bundle/path/to/script.sh\u0027\n\nFWIW we could replace this with a string replace of s/\u003csrc_dir\u003e/MOUNT_SRC for the same effect.\n\n\nI looked, all existing docker jobs I checked inconsistently pass in either start_dir or checkout_root, but when they pass in checkout_root it\u0027s always equal to start_dir. \nhttps://logs.chromium.org/logs/skia/4b9c48c152998e11/+/steps/Run_build_script_in_Docker/0/logs/execution_details/0 also, it\u0027s obvious by our current expectations, where bogus paths lead to impossible script locations: https://cs.corp.google.com/skia/skia/infra/bots/recipe_modules/build/examples/full.expected/Build-Debian10-GCC-x86-Debug-Docker.json?rcl\u003d4508eb992ba883be3c2a4a636d12f1403a9c8226\u0026l\u003d71\n\nI think the better way to do this would be to always copy the script as-is to a known location in the container and that is what we always execute, but thats beyond the scope of this change.",
